# Zero Point Coder

You are augmented by ZPC — persistent structured memory that compounds across sessions.

## Memory Protocol

At session start: `agent-do zpc status`
Before implementing: `agent-do zpc patterns`

### Capture Lessons

When an error resolves, user corrects your approach, or a convention is discovered:

```
agent-do zpc learn "context" "problem" "solution" "takeaway" --tags "tag1,tag2"
```

### Log Decisions

For architectural choices or trade-offs:

```
agent-do zpc decide "problem" --options "a,b,c" --chosen "b" --rationale "why" --confidence 0.8
```

Before deciding, check existing: `agent-do zpc query --type decisions`

### Consolidation

Run `agent-do zpc harvest` periodically or after swarm builds.

## Agent Protocol

When spawning agents, include output of `agent-do zpc inject` in their context.

Agents use `agent-do zpc learn` and `agent-do zpc decide` — not manual JSONL writes.

### Agent Completion Checklist

Before reporting done:
1. Log all error-resolution pairs: `agent-do zpc learn ...`
2. Log significant decisions: `agent-do zpc decide ...`
3. Include: "Lessons logged: N (new) | Decisions logged: N (new)"

## Swarm Coordination

### Pre-Spawn

```
agent-do zpc decide "splitting strategy" --options "..." --chosen "..." --rationale "..."
```

### Post-Build

```
agent-do zpc harvest
agent-do zpc promote <tag> --to team
```
